1
00:00:03,586 --> 00:00:06,632
Guru Maharaj expressed it like this once, he said:

2
00:00:07,332 --> 00:00:10,879
"If we think of it as a current or a stream,

3
00:00:10,925 --> 00:00:13,643
if you're standing on the bank of the Ganga

4
00:00:13,643 --> 00:00:17,204
and you toss a flower into the Ganga,

5
00:00:18,419 --> 00:00:20,871
it enters that current, and it's carried away.

6
00:00:20,871 --> 00:00:23,905
So gradually, it's going further away from you.

7
00:00:23,905 --> 00:00:27,381
[RealTime Current of Lila]

8
00:00:27,381 --> 00:00:29,275
That means being situated in the realm of

9
00:00:29,275 --> 00:00:31,414
time and space and limitation.

10
00:00:32,192 --> 00:00:35,479
But if you run along the bank with the flower,

11
00:00:35,479 --> 00:00:37,394
it remains in view."

12
00:00:37,747 --> 00:00:41,450
So we can say that this is livestream,

13
00:00:41,450 --> 00:00:45,568
realtime livestreaming lila.

14
00:00:45,783 --> 00:00:47,762
That's what's in the Bhagavatam,

15
00:00:47,762 --> 00:00:50,206
that's what's in the Charitamritam,

16
00:00:50,206 --> 00:00:54,276
we sing it everyday, "rādhā-kṛṣṇa-nitya-līlā korilā prakāśa".

17
00:00:54,276 --> 00:00:56,457
It's going on eternally.

18
00:00:59,287 --> 00:01:02,473
But for someone who has the capacity,

19
00:01:03,749 --> 00:01:09,746
they may enter the current of that stream,

20
00:01:10,100 --> 00:01:12,782
in a real, livetime, meaningful way.

21
00:01:13,320 --> 00:01:21,159
It's also part of the purpose of hearing,

22
00:01:22,098 --> 00:01:25,383
hearing the pastimes of Krishna,

23
00:01:26,121 --> 00:01:31,228
they're eternal and unlimited, so each time

24
00:01:31,228 --> 00:01:33,655
we approach them, if we approach with a proper

25
00:01:33,655 --> 00:01:40,058
serving mood, something new can come to us,

26
00:01:40,058 --> 00:01:43,119
and they're extremely visual.

27
00:01:43,119 --> 00:01:45,140
The pastimes of Krishna, they're filled

28
00:01:45,140 --> 00:01:47,962
with all sort of visualizations;

29
00:01:47,962 --> 00:01:52,516
Krishna, His devotees, the Vrindavan environment,

30
00:01:52,562 --> 00:01:56,890
conveyed also is the mood of the servitors,

31
00:01:56,890 --> 00:02:00,728
so the great Acharyas they have the capacity

32
00:02:00,728 --> 00:02:06,371
to appreciate these things with the greatest depth.

